column1: Will Iraq form a government before 21 February 2023?

column6: While it seemed like a mistake on his part, Sadr pulling out appears to have enabled the government formation process to go ahead. It looks like al-Sudani is doing surprisingly well at uniting the remaining political groups. I expect a government will be formed before 21 Feb, regardless of what Sadr does from the outside. There may well be further elections soon, but my hunch is that a majority of the Council of Representatives will approve of al-Sudani's proposed cabinet before the disunity causes things to fall apart again.
They haven't formed a government yet, and have had since the middle of October 2021, so that's twelve months. 21st February is four months away, another 20% of time.
